            <title>[SOLR-7266] The IgnoreCommitOptimizeUpdateProcessor blocks commit requests from replicas needing to recover.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7266</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The IgnoreCommitOptimizeUpdateProcessor introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6761&quot; title=&quot;Ability to ignore commit and optimize requests from clients when running in SolrCloud mode.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-6761&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-6761&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; prevents replicas from requesting the leader to commit during recovery. The processor should allow commit requests to pass through if the DistributedUpdateProcessor.COMMIT_END_POINT parameter == true.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
